00:36:13.100 --> 00:36:17.980
Some years ago, a prominent
writer from my country asked me,

00:36:17.980 --> 00:36:20.460
why do you plan to
publish a book with a title

00:36:20.460 --> 00:36:23.630
of The Forest of Birches?

00:36:23.630 --> 00:36:27.530
In Venezuela, evidently,
we don't have birches

00:36:27.530 --> 00:36:30.040
or snow or [inaudible].

00:36:31.700 --> 00:36:36.340
He said, you should write about
what you know, about real life,

00:36:36.340 --> 00:36:40.230
about your difficulties of
finding a house is Caracas,

00:36:40.230 --> 00:36:44.020
about being sad and poor.

00:36:44.020 --> 00:36:49.520
So, one day you will discover
that you must face and deal

00:36:49.520 --> 00:36:53.100
with stupid people who
use an abject nationalism

00:36:53.100 --> 00:36:55.530
to keep you in your place.

00:36:55.530 --> 00:36:58.970
Classists are as
uncomfortable with themselves

00:36:58.970 --> 00:37:03.090
as with the rest of the world.

00:37:03.090 --> 00:37:06.260
For me, first as a reader,
and then as a writer,

00:37:06.260 --> 00:37:10.880
opening my arms and my mind
was the most obvious approach.

00:37:10.880 --> 00:37:14.280
My national boundaries
were a blur

00:37:14.280 --> 00:37:16.970
between [inaudible]
coordinates that sooner

00:37:16.970 --> 00:37:20.480
or later will become part of
my most intimate landscape.

00:37:20.480 --> 00:37:26.780
Sometimes I get to like the
person I am and that's thanks

00:37:26.780 --> 00:37:29.010
to the poets of my country.

00:37:29.010 --> 00:37:33.230
Eugenio Montejo, Juan
Sanchez Pelaez who was here

00:37:33.230 --> 00:37:40.290
in the residency in Iowa,
[inaudible], just to name a few,

00:37:40.290 --> 00:37:44.960
but I'm also Elliott, Blake,
Milton, [inaudible] Brodsky,

00:37:44.960 --> 00:37:48.470
especially Brodsky,
especially Broksky, [inaudible]

00:37:48.470 --> 00:37:54.630
and also Iranian music, and the
Irish [inaudible] and colors

00:37:54.630 --> 00:37:57.100
and flavors that
scare or confuse

00:37:57.100 --> 00:37:59.300
but suddenly give you
back to the kitchen

00:37:59.300 --> 00:38:00.600
of your own grandmother.

00:38:00.600 --> 00:38:07.100
We should go beyond
the act of surviving.

00:38:07.100 --> 00:38:11.620
We should grab the life that,
that life is an act of terror

00:38:11.620 --> 00:38:16.860
and integrating beauty in the
ethical and aesthetic sense.

00:38:16.860 --> 00:38:19.590
Overcoming the always
new barrier of cynicism

00:38:19.590 --> 00:38:21.670
and disappointment,
demands sharpen

00:38:21.670 --> 00:38:25.350
and arise every moment
the [inaudible] diversity

00:38:25.350 --> 00:38:28.220
in front of us.

00:38:28.220 --> 00:38:32.450
And now [inaudible] I will
hate sound like a self-help

00:38:32.450 --> 00:38:37.490
or political correctness
preacher, but I am not wrong,

00:38:37.490 --> 00:38:39.170
I know I am not wrong.

00:38:39.170 --> 00:38:45.390
The eternal question about
identity also depends

00:38:45.390 --> 00:38:48.970
on the fact that we are many
in search of the same answer

00:38:48.970 --> 00:38:53.360
and on the way, it can be fun
and stimulating to recognize

00:38:53.360 --> 00:38:56.720
that spark of similarity
and difference.

00:38:56.720 --> 00:38:59.570
It is good to feel that
you belong to a place

00:38:59.570 --> 00:39:03.370
but it is much better if you
can expand that landscape

00:39:03.370 --> 00:39:05.700
and [inaudible] mysteries
from another universe.

00:39:05.700 --> 00:39:11.490
During my time of
International Writing Program,

00:39:11.490 --> 00:39:15.960
I saw how people love their own
language and at the same time,

00:39:15.960 --> 00:39:20.380
develop new facets of themselves
in a temporary language.

00:39:20.380 --> 00:39:23.110
Each contrast is
a new perspective

00:39:23.110 --> 00:39:26.360
that allows the [inaudible]
to visit new regions

00:39:26.360 --> 00:39:28.800
of their spiritual framework.

00:39:28.800 --> 00:39:34.230
Writers, we are not easy
people but I think that most

00:39:34.230 --> 00:39:38.300
of us start from the
fundamental conviction,

00:39:38.300 --> 00:39:42.330
nothing important can be
accomplished without tolerance,

00:39:42.330 --> 00:39:45.650
without the divine curiosity
that allows us to knock

00:39:45.650 --> 00:39:48.450
on a door and peek through.

00:39:48.450 --> 00:39:53.910
In Iowa I have the opportunity
to translate into Spanish poems

00:39:53.910 --> 00:39:57.540
by authors that I have found
on my way and to listen

00:39:57.540 --> 00:39:59.320
to my own work in
other languages.

00:39:59.320 --> 00:40:02.580
A poem of mine in
Japanese was one

00:40:02.580 --> 00:40:06.760
of the happiest revelations
of my life so far.

00:40:06.760 --> 00:40:09.940
So, once again, it
is clear to me

00:40:09.940 --> 00:40:13.810
that literature is a human
act and therefore political,

00:40:13.810 --> 00:40:18.240
not because of its
implication or etiological uses,

00:40:18.240 --> 00:40:22.100
but because it teaches us
nothing more and nothing less

00:40:22.100 --> 00:40:25.210
than what we are made
of alone and together.

00:40:25.210 --> 00:40:27.010
Thank you.

